-- Hong Kong Shares Fall as Hang Seng Heads for Weekly Drop
-- B y   A n n a   K i t a n a k a
-- 2013-05-16T01:46:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/hong-kong-shares-fall-as-hang-seng-heads-for-weekly-drop.html
Hong Kong  shares  fell, led by
developers, as the city’s benchmark equity index headed toward
its first weekly drop in four weeks.  The  Hang Seng Index  lost 0.2 percent 23,002.81 as of 9:34
a.m. in Hong Kong, heading toward a 1.3 percent decline this
week. The city’s markets are shut tomorrow for a holiday. The
Hang Seng China Enterprises Index of mainland shares lost 1.1
percent to 10,965.38 today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anna Kitanaka in Tokyo at 
 akitanaka@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
